    public static interface ValueFactory.TransparentBuilder<V,C extends V,A extends C,J extends C,B extends V,M extends V,N extends V,S extends V>
extends ValueFactory<V,C,A,A,J,J,B,M,N,S>
    A ValueFactory with transparent array and object builders.

    ValueFactory defines separate types for JSON array and object builders vs arrays and objects themselves. That is useful for an API like JSR-374. However, in other APIs there is no distinction to be made. A TransparentBuilder is a ValueFactory whose JSON array builders and arrays are the same instance of the same class, and whose JSON object builders and objects are the same instance of the same class.

    Since:
    2019-09-01
    Author:
    jsonurl.org, David MacCormack
